EDINBURGH, Scotland (AP) — Scotland will be able to have a full house for its Six Nations rugby opener against England at Murrayfield next month after its government announced Tuesday a lifting of restrictions on crowds at outdoor sporting events from Jan. 17.A limit of 500 spectators had been imposed three weeks ago in a bid to deal with a surge of the omicron variant of the coronavirus.Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon confirmed the lifting of restrictions in a statement to the Scottish Parliament. She said the guidance will be for at least 50% of spectators to have their vaccination status checked and that COVID-19 certification will now only be valid with a booster.Scotland will host two games at the 67,000-capacity Murrayfield in the Six Nations — against England on Feb. 5 and France on Feb. 26.___More AP rugby: https://apnews.com/hub/rugby and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports